title: Dynamic Neuromuscular Stabilization (DNS)
content: Dynamic Neuromuscular Stabilization (DNS) is based on a re-engineering of the development of movement patterns that occurs between three months of age and walking. It was originally developed to help kids with cerebral palsy, but is now used to help anyone with movement deficiencies. Although Beth likes the concept of DNS, she is not as familiar with it as other disciplines and does not use it as much.
